tle><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/e00pyI3</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/K4IivG8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/g432msy.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eEUceRr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/cerjaDk.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Cat tax. 

My parents didn't even let me have the books in the 1st place. I had to invent my own system using the only dice I owned (a d12 and a d6) and disguise my GMing with friends in my room as listening to music. As a result our adventures were heavily influenced by The Cure (we went to school with that band and it was considered OK as they were 'nice young christian men') and Bauhaus (my parents couldn't tell the difference between their music) and Siouxsie and the Banshees (my parents figured if we were listening to a 'girl band' we were not up to 'sinful gay stuff'... jokes on them I turned out super-queer), with plotlines stolen from Dramarama, Into the Labyrinth, and Marmalade Atkins.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
For those interested in my home-brew rules having only been exposed to D&D through word-of-mouth: 
You had 12 points to spend between three 'stats', but you could pick what your stats were called. If you had a stat that was relevant to something you rolled a d12 and tried to get under or equal to your stat number, and if you rolled exactly on the stat something really cool happened. If you didn't have a relevant stat then you rolled a d6 and on an even you just about succeeded but on an odd something bad happened. 
Everything bad had 1d6+6 hit points, dragons had 2d12+12 hit points, and adventurers started each day with 1d6+12 hit points. 
Plate and/or magic armor subtracted 1d6 from the damage of enemy attacks, if you were wearing no armor it added 2 to the damage of enemy attacks. Adventurers and dragons did 1d12 damage, regular monsters did 1d6 damage. All attacks automatically hit.
As far as I can recall we had no concept of things like experience points, levels, etc so character improvement was through finding magic weapons or learning spells. 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Our adventures revolved around a travelling circus, and fighting dragons who were trying to build dungeons.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/e00pyI3</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ThatOtherGirlYouKnow]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Never a dull moment</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/X7wYO7M</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/K6NAUAY.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Plz comment below if you know original OP</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/X7wYO7M</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[CanWeStopTalkingNow]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>BEHOLD.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/HloP6HX</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/07kewqT.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Fun stuff…send something pleasant.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/HloP6HX</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[deafkitten]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Internet Gifts - “Special Edition” Pt. 5</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/sEWRUxl</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/aNzz9tY.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kYqcYk6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>2.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/10cUn0k.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>3.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qqFxsQM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>4.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/m30ECBt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>5.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/cBkAO4p.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>6.</div><div><img alt="" src="htt